INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (359101, 'The right priorities in planning will help you to avoid fuss, tiredness and overwork', 3800, 0), (359102, 'Truth is always right, observing it guarantees us victory in life.', 3800, 0), (359103, 'Righteousness gives a person the right to God’s protection.', 3800, 0), (359104, 'No knowledge comes to you late. It comes just at the time when you are ready for it.', 5073, 0), (359105, 'If I formed the questions correctly, then perhaps the immediate answer might be in the vein of earlier responses to questions of what is right or wrong; that is, that there is not a clear-cut answer. What is certain is that avowed Christians were among the Founding-Fathers and, by way of the resulting documents and discourse, did influence the formation of a new nation…under God. And while some may have held to the new nation as a ''City upon the Hill'', others may have realized the marked difference between man’s government and that of God.', 24601, 0), (359106, 'A lot went wrong before I ended up in a great place!', 1581, 0), (359107, 'He''s got that way of believing his opinion is the truth, but he''s not disagreeable about it. He''s too sure he''s right to bother being disagreeable.', 866, 0), (359108, 'Immediate necessity makes many things convenient, which if continued would grow into oppressions. Expedience and right are different things.', 1131, 0), (359109, 'To do a great right, you may do a little wrong; and you may take any means which the end to be attained will justify.', 96, 0), (359110, 'Lord lead us to the right places.', 2878, 0), (359111, 'It is better to have little and be right than to have much and be wrong.', 2878, 0), (359112, 'If certain places you came to in life felt right, then how many others were just as clearly the wrong place to be?', 23364, 0), (359113, 'When it''s right it''s never too late, when it''s wrong it''s always too soon', 14987, 0), (359114, 'Wrong is wrong even if everyone is doing it. Right is right even if no one is doing it.', 57671, 0), (359115, 'If you are inefficient, you have a right to be afraid of the consequences.', 11078, 0), (359116, 'I am longing to show him my love, but not by doing what is wrong', 6611, 0), (359117, 'God condemns those who oppress and take advantage of others.', 4239, 0), (359118, 'Doing the right thing irl (in real life) or online is good netiquette, but it is not always easy. NetworkEtiquette.net', 25359, 0), (359119, 'He sighed. "Does it get tiring?""What?""Always thinking you''re right."I smiled. "No, not really. It''s other people not realizing I''m right that gets tiring.', 2355, 0), (359120, 'He will only do the wrong thing when it''s the right thing to do..', 2433, 0), (359121, 'Sometimes people try to expose what''s wrong with you, because they can''t handle what''s right about you.', 11230, 0), (359122, 'Never joined the wrong boat. When the destination is right, and the direction is wronged, everything goes wrongly!', 3301, 0), (359123, 'Your fright is in your lies but your delight is in your ties,So better get together and fight for the right.', 38432, 0), (359124, 'Let all things be done in order, with right and decency. Those things are worth a man''s life or two. Life without would be a hell, indeed.', 6934, 0), (359125, 'It is good to say something beautiful; it is even better to say something right; but saying a right thing beautifully, that is the best!', 3701, 0), (359126, 'For the right woman? I''d like to think I''d do just about anything.', 7855, 0), (359127, 'Don''t chase people. Be yourself, do your own thing and work hard. The right people will come to you and stay.', 11230, 0), (359128, 'People need to have "the dignity of risk" and "the right to fail".', 57672, 0), (359129, 'Love is always a surprise and you never get it right.', 10053, 0), (359130, 'You can''t make people right by making them feel wrong!', 7030, 0), (359131, 'Someone else doesn’t have to be wrong for you to be right.', 7030, 0), (359132, 'By what right do I bend men to my will? Or is there no right, only ability?', 2418, 0), (359133, 'I don''t need every answer. Just the right answer.', 26397, 0), (359134, 'Don’t be disappointed, the winning side is not always the right one.', 4238, 0), (359135, 'Doing something wrong repeatedly does not make it right.', 6254, 0), (359136, 'Right and wrong are very complicated', 57673, 0), (359137, 'You have right to be angry, insult and slap. But later you have to forgive.', 4238, 0), (359138, 'Finding the right one is never easy. Especially, when the wrong one looks so right.', 57674, 0), (359139, 'Our natural rights come from an authority beyond the petty rule of man.', 7223, 0), (359140, 'When everything was right, something was bound to go wrong. (Jessica)', 6463, 0), (359141, 'The prosperity of right is that it is always beautiful and pure.', 98, 0), (359142, 'The only one who can make two wrongs equal a right, is He who works all things together!" HS/el', 3408, 0), (359143, 'If you can hold back, judge people and differentiate between right and wrong you are not in love.', 4238, 0), (359144, 'I know two kinds of Christians, those that love and those that love to be right.', 57675, 0), (359145, 'It''s just that life felt the right size in there... not too big and not too small. Wasn''t so hard to work up a bit of courage. It''s got so bloody complicated since then.', 9896, 0), (359146, 'There is always a right answer for every question, even for the wrong ones.', 4238, 0), (359147, 'Always the right question is considered the unrelated one.', 4238, 0), (359148, 'For a quite good time I thought it''s impossible for I to be right with an ideology which a group of people disagree with. Later on I was assured that I was wrong about that idea.', 30811, 0), (359149, 'Being over there changes a man. Right and wrong don''t look so different anymore to some.', 1760, 0), (359150, 'The end justifies the means. Sometimes you have to do the wrong thing to get the right result.', 57676, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (359151, 'No man can have a right to impose an unchosen obligation , an unrewarded duty or an involuntary servitude on another man.There can be no such thing as " the right to enslave .', 631, 0), (359152, 'I fear nothing when I am doing right,'' said Jack.''Then,'' said the lady in the red cap, ''you are one of those who slay giants.', 9606, 0), (359153, 'But more than that, if you ally yourself with people who are prepared to fight to make a difference, then your life will always be in danger. I don''t think it''s fair to ever blame the person who makes the stand. Because the Doctor''s so old, because he''s done this so many times before, he sometimes forgets how dangerous it is. But if he didn''t create the danger by opposing evil, if he didn''t get these people to help him, then terrible things would happen. Standing up for what''s right is always the best thing to do.', 57677, 0), (359154, 'The word ''heresy'' not only means no longer being wrong', 57678, 0), (359155, 'Right is just and true.', 98, 0), (359156, 'Right now is always the right time for almost everything.', 32964, 0), (359157, 'I find there are usually no extremes in relationships, even friendship. One is not always right or never wrong.', 57679, 0), (359158, 'Why is it that we are constantly proving the world wrong but never proving ourselves right?', 32973, 0), (359159, 'He may have as strong a sense of what would be right, as you can have, without being so equal under particular circumstances to act up to it.""Then, it would not be so strong a sense. If it failed to produce equal exertion, it could not be an equal conviction.', 24, 0), (359160, 'It was one of those March days when the sun shines hot and the wind blows cold: when it is summer in the light, and winter in the shade.', 96, 0), (359161, 'I will be the gladdest thing under the sun! I will touch a hundred flowers and not pick one.', 106, 0), (359162, 'Can you see the sunset real good on the West side? You can see it on the East side too.', 1433, 0), (359163, 'Here I came to the very edge where nothing at all needs saying, everything is absorbed through weather and the sea, and the moon swam back, its rays all silvered, and time and again the darkness would be broken by the crash of a wave, and every day on the balcony of the sea, wings open, fire is born, and everything is blue again like morning. ', 12, 0), (359164, 'He stepped down, avoiding any long look at her as one avoids long looks at the sun, but seeing her as one sees the sun, without looking.', 93, 0), (359165, 'Whenever she turned her steep focus to me, I felt the warmth that flowers must feel when they bloom through the snow, under the first concentrated rays of the sun.', 524, 0), (359166, 'The sun just touched the morning;	The morning, happy thing,	Supposed that he had come to dwell,	And life would be all spring.', 91, 0), (359167, 'Why''s it so sunny?" she repeated.Zooey observed her rather narrowly. "I bring the sun wherever I go, buddy," he said.', 268, 0), (359168, 'See," Sasha muttered, eyeing the sun. "It''s mine.', 2412, 0), (359169, 'Do you see that out there? The strange, unfamiliar light? It''s called the sun. Let''s go get us a little.', 466, 0), (359170, 'I am alive, and drunk on sunlight.', 169, 0), (359171, 'The patter of tentative footfalls reached my ears. I flipped on my side to face the door and saw Ansel wander by. I rolled onto my back, rubbing sleep from my eyes. I''d crashed on my bed as soons as I''d gotten back from school, collapsing under the weight of the day. The floorboards squeaked as Ansel passed by my door again. I caught his nervous glance in my direction before he hurried down the hall. ''Ansel, I''m not the sun; stop orbiting and get in here,'' I called.', 10842, 0), (359172, 'Too much sun after a Syracuse winter does strange things to your head, makes you feel strong, even if you aren''t.', 1421, 0), (359173, 'Have you noticed how many people who walk in the shade curse the Sun?', 4860, 0), (359174, 'Look at the sun! It’s dry, it’s dead, it needs a drink, it wants blood! And I’ll give it blood!', 4004, 0), (359175, 'Just let them sit in the goddam sun. But the world won''t let them because there''s nothing more dangerous than letting old farts sit in the sun. They might be thinking. Same thing with kids. Keep ''em busy or they might start thinking.', 20529, 0), (359176, 'The weather turned. Her skin seemed to grow a million extra pores, and all of them opened to take in the warmth and tenderness of the air. The sun on her face made her want to cry. Into all those millions of open pores came the sunshine, and other feelings as well. In and out. She was porous.', 256, 0), (359177, '- Do you want to know why I followed you into that funeral parlor?- You said you followed me on a whim.- That´s the truth, but there´s more to it. I was parking at the gas station across the street and I saw you get out of your car. I didn´t think much of it until you pausen on your way inside the shop. You tilted your head toward the sun and closed your eyes, like a prisoner stepping outside after years of being locked away. It seemed so odd. No one just stops and appreciates life like that, but you did. I could see your smile from across the street and I couldn´t look away. I knew in that moment that I was completely uninterested in pursuing a life in wich I didn´t cross that street and meet you.', 40858, 0), (359178, 'As the sun does not wait for prayers and incantations tob e induced to rise, but immediately shines and is saluted by all, so do you also not wait for clappings of hands and shouts of praise tob e induced to do good, but be a doer of good voluntarily and you will be beloved as much as the sun.', 1328, 0), (359179, 'Love you always, miss you always... running day and night, leaving the place of sun and moon, of ice and snow.Never look back, never forget.', 2381, 0), (359180, 'What a great thing, to be loved! What a greater thing still, to love! The heart becomes heroic though passion…if no one loved, the sun would go out.', 98, 0), (359181, 'It is more or less a given that nothing is less favorable to clairvoyance than the bright sun: physical light and mental light coexist on very poor terms.', 168, 0), (359182, 'The sun was as flirty as Scarlett O''Hara with the Tarleton twins, breaking through the clouds in spectacular bursts that seemed like personal favors and then retreating for hours, days, and making us all ache for just a glimpse.', 20158, 0), (359183, 'In the midst of all dwells the Sun. For who could set this luminary in another or better place in this most glorious temple, than whence he can at one and the same time brighten the whole.', 4674, 0), (359184, 'And each one there has one thing shared;They have sweated beneath the same sun,Look up in wonder at the same moon,And wept when it was all done,For being done too soon.', 37497, 0), (359185, 'The sun was a toddler insistently refusing to go to bed.', 9, 0), (359186, 'The Sun has no chance to be nobody and that is the punishment for being a sun! If you can be nobody just like a humble tree in a silent forest, you can find the happiness too!', 3701, 0), (359187, 'The sun had bled away every smell and left nothing.', 578, 0), (359188, 'In the future, man will be able to create an artificial Sun which is very similar to the Sun in the sky that was once upon a time worshipped as a god!', 3701, 0), (359189, 'The foundational Vajrakilaya is the sun shining in the sky behind the clouds. The path Vajrakilaya is the removal of the clouds from the sky through the force of wind and rain, or whatever; it is the path of method and wisdom, combined. And the resultant Vajrakilaya is the nature of your mind, the nature of your rigpa, which is the same mind as the mind of the primordial buddha, Kuntuzangpo. The path Vajrakilaya is the removal of the adventitious veil of obscuration that covers rigpa. Applying the method by practicing generation stage (kyerim) and completion stage (dzogrim), accumulating merit and purifying negative karma, removing that veil, is the path. The result is realizing that ones own self nature is buddha. So the result is the same as the foundation. In the beginning you are buddha, and in the end you are buddha.', 57680, 0), (359190, 'This morning, the sun endures past dawn. I realise that it is August: the summer''s last stand.', 10341, 0), (359191, 'Every time you shudder from the cold or wrap yourself more tightly in your furs, it reminds me that somewhere, the sun shines more brightly than it does here. You carry it in your skin.', 57681, 0), (359192, 'What if the Sun says that I am bored of doing the same tasks again and again everyday.', 57682, 0), (359193, 'When the sun goes out, it will be your love that keeps we warm.', 2876, 0), (359194, 'When you''re in love, the sun never stops shining.', 2876, 0), (359195, 'Each day the sun kisses the day goodnight yet no two days are alike.', 12025, 0), (359196, 'Each day the sun kisses the earth goodnight yet now two sunsets are alike', 12025, 0), (359197, 'I was born in the middle of a stormYou won''t find me under the sunMy feet are chaosI belong to the wild things', 4545, 0), (359198, 'And of a Sunday swarm the folkUnder the honeysuckle vine, Quaffing, the while they talk and smoke, The sun, the melody, the wine.', 4453, 0), (359199, 'i like your embraces because the vertigo smells like the sun.', 7137, 0), (359200, 'Hail the sun! the brightest of all that everDawned on the City of Seven Gates, City of Thebes!Hail the golden dawn over Dirce''s riverRising to speed the flight of the white invaders Homeward in full retreat!" - Chorus', 139, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (359201, 'It was one of those sweltering summer days in which the air itself seems to decline as a haze suffocates the outside world. It is painfully bright whether you are looking up at that ball of burning hydrogen or down at its vivid reflection on sheer pavement.', 7672, 0), (359202, 'Between shortage and absolute poverty an ocean of shades and gradations do emerge on the scale of deficiency. Be that as it may, each stage must find a mode to leave a door ajar for the sun to peer in and human warmth to radiate. ( " Homeless down in the corner")', 2711, 0), (359203, 'Spring is the time of the year when it is summer in the sun and winter in the shade', 96, 0), (359204, 'I have looked at the sun. It is so shinny, so hot. Attracted me but made me blind. Burned me. I went to the shadow. Under a tree. I could see clearly. I cooled down.', 6349, 0), (359205, 'Nothing is more on the nose,than sun cream.', 2876, 0), (359206, 'When the Root and Branch were young, when the Rose still grew unplucked upon the tree; when all our lands were new and green and we danced without care, then, we were immortal... We left those lands for the world where time dwells, dancing, that we might see the passage of the sun and the growing of the world. Here we may die, and where we can fall, and here King ___ has stopped his dancing.', 3385, 0), (359207, 'There is a particular kind of afternoon sun that exists only in autumn. A golden light drapes itself over the world of that hour. It falls through the afternoon sky, fine and faint as a swirl of cigarette smoke caught in the wind, nearly transparent. So sweet, that light, insisting softly, goldly against the windows.', 27458, 0), (359208, 'The sun is setting on the New Republic,” Leia said. “It''s time for the Resistance to rise.', 597, 0), (359209, 'After making sure that the terrain would be undisputedly its own, the sun slowly and majestically emerged from its resting place and established absolute dominion in a matter of seconds, blissfully unaware that its conquest would not last for more than a day. Its swift triumph was marked by an explosion of radiance which overawed nature for a brief moment; therewith an orgy of birdsong, corrupted by sporadic and pretentious cocks'' crowing, marked the beginning of another day.', 57683, 0), (359210, 'This is the life you''re living. It''s not temporary and it''s not pretend and there''s no do-over.', 470, 0), (359211, 'The sea, like a crinkled chart, spread to the horizon, and lapped the sharp outline of the coast, while the houses were white shells in a rounded grotto, pricked here and there by a great orange sun.', 1214, 0), (359212, 'We are spirits deceived by the sky to create light and trade our souls to the sun but fail to become galaxies when it''s dark', 10325, 0), (359213, 'He needed the warmth of the sun to take away the chill of foreboding that grew in him.', 514, 0), (359214, 'The orbit of every planet is an ellipse with the sun at one of the two foci.', 13386, 0), (359215, 'How about peaches, dear?” murmurs Madame Manec, and Marie-Laure can hear a can opening, juice slopping into a bowl. Seconds later, she’s eating wedges of wet sunlight.', 1202, 0), (359216, 'Don''t look at the sun, but rather what it illuminates.', 57684, 0), (359217, 'Winter teetered on the verge of succumbing to the returning sun, but today the breeze still preferred the touch of snowflakes', 32608, 0), (359218, 'Tell me the story about how the sun loved the moon so much that he died every night to let her breathe.', 33, 0), (359219, 'It is so small a thing to have enjoyed the sun, to have lived light in the spring, to have loved, to have thought, to have done.', 460, 0), (359220, 'Dear sun i agree you are very "HOT"; you don''t have to prove it everyday', 47461, 0), (359221, 'He threw his hands to his eyes and hissed. Like the hiss of incinerating ashes. "What is this bright, orange orb in the sky that mocks me with its warmth?', 22208, 0), (359222, '~Seasons of Life~When the sunburn I blind,When the sky showers I cover,When the wind blows I blanket,When the death calls I undergo,When would I experience the nature?', 6666, 0), (359223, 'melanin touchesyour eyes like thesun kissed bliss ofmankind', 57685, 0), (359224, 'Every time I looked at the sky and at my watch, that monster was still up there.', 57686, 0), (359225, 'The way we envision the stars is by imagining they''re attached to a giant invisible sphere surrounding the earth. It is a total fiction, really - just a construction we came up with to help us get our heads around the complexity of it all ... The ecliptic, put simply is the plane of the earth''s orbit around the sun. But since we all live here on earth, we observe the sun to be moving along this plane instead. Why? Because what would be the point of looking at things from the perspective of the sun? That''s no use to anyone ... Ergo, it''s an imaginary circle, as it''s only a part of our human construction of the cosmos.', 7356, 0), (359226, 'You can order the sun to come up if you time it right. I’m not driving this bus. Making it do what I want would be like talking someone out of a seizure.', 13363, 0), (359227, 'For the to see you shine, you must stay far way, for you are like the sun; when you’re too close, your light make them blind. And when you’re too far, they seek you. So let them seek you. They’re getting your light regardless, but appreciating your presence is different from recognizing your existence. If they don’t appreciate your presence, they may never recognize your absence.', 2064, 0), (359228, 'Because becoming suns to enlighten other people''s faded suns is really worth it', 6064, 0), (359229, 'When people close to me lie to me or try manipulating me, I feel like I know how the sun feels when the clouds steal the sun''s thunder.', 43741, 0), (359230, 'The sun beasts the shit out of a dirty road called Raton Pass where the closest thing to a pair of matching earring is a guy named Carl who punches you in the head with his fist.', 10897, 0), (359231, 'Stand tall with your feet on the ground, feel the earth under your feet and raise your head towards the sun. Take in its warmth and carry it with you. When you feel cold with fear, when you feel alone and lost, look to the sun, close your eyes and let it warm your heart, let it feed your soul, let it remind you of your divinity.” –Betsy Chasse', 57687, 0), (359232, 'I tear down Baxter, which loops around the last mile down to Back Cove.And then I stop short. The buildings have fallen away behind me, giving way to ramshackle sheds, sparsely situated on either side of the cracked and run-down road. Beyond that, a short strip of tall, weedy grass slants down toward the cove.The water is an enormous mirror, tipped with pink and gold from the sky. In that single, blazing moment as I come around the bend, the sun—curved over the dip of the horizon like a solid gold archway—lets out its final winking rays of light, shattering the darkness of the water, turning everything white for a fraction of a second, and then falls away, sinking, dragging the pink and the red and the purple out of the sky with it, all the color bleeding away instantly and leaving only dark.Alex was right. It was gorgeous—one of the best I’ve ever seen.', 82, 0), (359233, 'You always have my attention. When you''re in the room, you''re my sun.', 22139, 0), (359234, 'We are inside this plasma,and plasma is inside everything. It is incandescentin the sun, and I am curious to know if youare able to stop orbiting yourself around it even for a second.No, you are not able to do this, but you are ableto stop the truths from being spoken.All the absurd things are cool. Their spirits losetheir oxygen ions to generatethat matter in no pain. The spiritual thingsare in pulsing metamorphosis to break into pieces, orto turn back aftera hard but reversing processbefore becoming anachronistic.', 20606, 0), (359235, 'SUMMER REVERIEThe sun’s sultry glow make me swift footedto explore the sea', 57688, 0), (359236, 'Had there been no sun, life would have found some other means of illuminating the world. It is odd that we give the sun so much importance.', 15136, 0), (359237, 'Be healthy by being outdoors in the natural daylight with nature!', 5008, 0), (359238, 'But there were certain early days in Casterbridge- days of firmamental exhaustion which followed angry south-westerly tempests-when, if the sun shone, the air was like velvet.', 552, 0), (359239, 'The sun from far gives life. But get close to it and it burns anything down to ashes', 23844, 0), (359240, 'Every end of the day is a great movie and the Sun above is surely the leading actor in this film!', 3701, 0), (359241, 'Filtering solar radiation with air pollution is a bad idea.', 5008, 0), (359242, 'That first winter, when it was time for her friends to leave, the girl ventured out into the show to say goodbye, and the stunning raven-haired Squaller handed her another gift. "A blue kefta," said the math teacher, shaking her head. "What would she do with ', 361, 0), (359243, 'Maddock stabbed his fried egg with his fork, and bright yellow yolk bled all over his plate like a sunshine hemorrhage.', 446, 0), (359244, 'The sun kept dipping down into the ocean and the lights came on at the harbor, casting sudden shadows on the ground, illuminating the faces that were just a second ago silhouettes. The sky was golden and purple, the ocean a darker shade of violet.', 2153, 0), (359245, 'The Egyptians saw the sun and called him Ra, the Sun God. He rode across the sky in his chariot until it was time to sleep. Copernicus and Galileo proved otherwise and poor Ra lost his divinity.', 22495, 0), (359246, 'When the sun touched the earth, it spread out along the horizon like a giant yolk oozing free of its skin.', 480, 0), (359247, 'The sun will rise whether you like it or not, whether you oppose it or not, whether you care about it or not! Some things will happen whatever you think and whatever you feel about them!', 3701, 0), (359248, 'Nothing was more powerful than the sun before it went down, nor more beautiful. She took a long deep breath. She could watch the sky for hours but then she knew that Mark really did deserve some sort of an answer.', 27133, 0), (359249, 'If you are a hope for someone, that’s very nice, but if you are a hope for everyone just like the Sun, that’s excellent!', 3701, 0), (359250, 'Life is a summer, full of fun, at the beach, under the sun.', 2586, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (359251, 'You must not waste your one day here. When the sun shines, you let it shine on you. Snow is always waiting.', 150, 0), (359252, 'I very carefully levered up an eyelid and shut it again fast. A merciless sunbeam had squirted straight in, making my brain bleed.', 17274, 0), (359253, 'After luncheon the sun, conscious that it was Saturday, would blaze an hour longer in the zenith,...', 450, 0), (359254, 'can you see how amazing the Sun in Winter? so beautiful like a miracle", and he looked at me and said "The Sun is like a miracle just in Winter, but you are a miracle in my life', 49537, 0), (359255, 'they''d become unaccustomed to the brightness of their own city, and, faced with it now in all its intensity, they cupped their hands over their eyes as if staring into the sun.', 309, 0), (359256, 'can you see how amazing the sun in Winter, like a miracle",i said. He looked at me and said "The sun is like miracle just in Winter and you are miracle in my life".', 12668, 0), (359257, '- Do you want to know why I followed you into that funeral parlor?- You said you followed me on a whim.- That´s the truth, but there´s more to it. I was parking at the gas station across the street and I saw you get out of your car. I didn´t think much of it until you paused on your way inside the shop. You tilted your head toward the sun and closed your eyes, like a prisoner stepping outside after years of being locked away. It seemed so odd. No one just stops and appreciates life like that, but you did. I could see your smile from across the street and I couldn´t look away. I knew in that moment that I was completely uninterested in pursuing a life in wich I didn´t cross that street and meet you', 40858, 0), (359258, 'can you see how amazing the Sun in Winter? so beautiful like a miracle", and he looked at me and said "The Sun is like a miracle just in Winter, but you are a mirace in my life".', 49537, 0), (359259, 'Never did an eye see the sun unless it had first become sun-like, and never can the soul have vision of the First Beauty unless itself be beautiful.', 36287, 0), (359260, 'Everyone can get the gold of the Sun. (Tout le monde cueille - L''or du soleil)', 23404, 0), (359261, 'Whenever the birds sing, I will remember you Claire. As long as the sun shines, I will love you. And when the sun darkens everything and the dead sky falls, I will hope to see life again, I will hope to see you. There was never much hope but a fool''s hope and a fool am I.', 25189, 0), (359262, 'Water shines under the sun. But the sun dries it. (Eau brille sous soleil - Qui pourtant l’assèche.)', 23404, 0), (359263, 'The silverware shines if the sun. (L''argenterie brille - Si le soleil.', 23404, 0), (359264, 'The river overflows, not the sun. (Déborde le fleuve, - Pas le soleil)', 23404, 0), (359265, 'Summer, dropping so easily a delicious everything upon your skin and lips. Like a never-ending kiss—taunting, deep, and luscious. The sun. The heat. The thousand echoes of a timelessness before time, when every day seems longer than the next and no day seems likely to ever truly end. Summer.', 23450, 0), (359266, 'Sun is a cosmic hand which tries to reach you wherever you are!', 3701, 0), (359267, 'It was one of those bitter mornings when the whole of nature is shiny, brittle, and hard, like crystal. The trees, decked out in frost, seem to have sweated ice; the earth resounds beneath one''s feet; the tiniest sounds carry a long way in the dry air; the blue sky is bright as a mirror, and the sun moves through space in icy brilliance, casting on the frozen world rays which bestow no warmth upon anything.', 1559, 0), (359268, 'ah yes I know them well who was the first person in the universe before there was anybody that made it all who ah that they dont know neither do I so there you are they might as well try to stop the sun from rising tomorrow the sun shines for you he said the day we were lying among the